-- ECB funding to Greek banks drops slightly in August
-- 
-- Thu Sep 11, 2014 10:17AM EDT
-- None



ATHENS, Sept 11 (Reuters) - European Central Bank (ECB) funding to Greek banks fell in August by 60 million euros, Greek central bank data showed on Thursday.

ECB funding dropped to 44.56 billion euros ($57.6 billion) from 44.62 billion euros in July.